<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Johnston, John. Description of the Country around Lakes Superior and Huron, 1809. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0018</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;">recovered from him the price of their time and labour: at the same time that the Noble Projectors would have had the honour of opening a new source of commerce and Riches to their Country, and would have made a large addition to their private fortunes in a manner the least exceptionable and of course the most worthy of such characters<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">After you leave the Bay of Miners you have a Point to double nearly similar to the last described, except that there is a <span class="DelHand-author">Small</span> <span class="AddHand-author">little</span> natural arch <span class="DelHand-author">where</span> <span class="AddHand-author">through</span> which you can pass in a small Canoe<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  You have now Grand Island opposite to you, which Stretches almost due North into the Lake<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  It is about three Leagues long and perhaps nine in circumference<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Soil on the Island is excellent, the timber chiefly Beech and Maple<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  It is the Summer Residence of a small Band of Indians who cultivate Maize Potatoes and Pumpkins<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">From the last point of the <span class="DelHand-author">S</span><span class="AddHand-author">C</span>ascades the rock continues nearly of an equal height for half a league and then Recedes in form of an Amphitheatre surrounding Grand Island bay which is completely land locked and forms the largest and safest Harbour upon the Lake<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The entr<span class="DelHand-author">i</span><span class="AddHand-author">a</span>nce is from the North east<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Island must be kept close aboard on entering the bay, to keep clear of a sandy Shoal which begins where the <span class="DelHand-author">S</span><span class="AddHand-author">C</span>ascades terminate and runs near a mile Right into the Channel, but is easil<span class="DelHand-author">e</span><span class="AddHand-author">y</span> avoided as part of it is above water<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[19]</span></p>

